Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: I have been trying to go through this thread to see if someone addressed this concern, but wow ... so many pages! Anyway, this looks like a project with tons of potential, my only concern was regarding a section on their whitepaper were they mention that: “Moreover, exchanging and spending Merchant Tokens and performing transactions from your smartphone wallet creates a variety of valuable data. This data can be bundled and sold to merchants and brands, ...” As much as I understand the benefit this gives to vendors and a lot of what we do is already being tracked probably, I am not a fan of my transaction data being sold to merchants and brands since one thing I appreciate from crypto-currency is the privacy it offers.  I do value that they have been honest by disclosing that info, but will there be an option for the consumer to opt out of this?

Author: revelacaogr
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Maximizing Sales with Micro Targeting: GATCOIN - Killer App for Retailers  https://cointelegraph.com/news/maximizing-sales-with-micro-targeting-gatcoin-killer-app-for-retailers  GATCOIN has identified how cryptocurrencies and tokens can revolutionize the experience of online shoppers. Their platform will make crypto solutions more accessible to the average online retailer. Other features will provide offline solutions to businesses, allowing retailers to seamlessly reach shoppers on their smartphones and to blend the online and in-store experiences.  GATCOIN will enable retailers to simply create their own tokens, which are more easily saved and promote more brand loyalty than conventional loyalty programs. It does not just involve a coin, but a platform of solutions that cover all aspects of adoption.The major elements of the platform include:  GAT Wallet: a mobile token wallet, shopping platform and payment portal GAT Marketplace: an online marketplace of participating merchant stores where merchant tokens can be used for products and services GAT Exchange: a full feature cryptocurrency exchange where members can trade merchant tokens for the GAT coins and trade GAT coins for other public cryptocurrencies such as Bitcoin and Ethereum or even cash. GAT Network: private consortia networks of high-speed, super large ledgers on which Merchant Tokens are circulated. This improves transaction speeds and thereby consumer satisfaction. Targeted A-DropTM Delivery System: a patent-pending cryptocurrency delivery system that allows merchants to airdrop tokens to specific groups of consumers by demographic, spending preference and geo-location........

Author: Rigorous
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: On the other hand, if you look at IPOs on the traditional stock exchanges there is the concept of underwriting.  Underwriting is the process by which investment bankers raise investment capital from investors on behalf of corporations and governments that are issuing either equity or debt securities. The word "underwriter" originally came from the practice of having each risk-taker write his name under the total amount of risk he was willing to accept at a specified premium.  An underwriter works closely with the issuing body to determine the offering price of the securities, buys them from the issuer, and sells them to investors via the underwriter's distribution network. Underwriters generally receive underwriting fees from their issuing clients, but they also can earn profits when selling the underwritten shares to investors.  http://www.investopedia.com/terms/u/underwriting.asp  So whether you call it fee, premium, discount or bonus, it is a reward for early buyer risk and providing liquidity.

They include:  Quote Cash tokens, which are used as pre-paid cash Discount tokens, which are used to subsidize the regular cash price of an item Loyalty tokens, which are used to replace loyalty points Gift tokens, which replace gift vouchers Travel tokens, which are used as portable currency to spend globally  Beyond that, the Gatcoin ecosystem features five key components:  Quote GAT Wallet: a mobile token wallet GAT Exchange: a cryptocurrency exchange where members can trade Merchant Tokens against GAT Coin GAT Network: private networks where Merchant Tokens are circulated Targeted A-Drop Delivery System: a proprietary system that allows retailers to target specific consumer demographics within minutes  Gatcoin is no small project, and it isn’t just popping up out of nowhere, either. The company has a very strong business case, as it prepares to roll out services across 60,000 retail stores and 21 brands throughout Asia.

Body: Thanks for all the support on here, friends! We're really excited with the results from the first day! The pre-sale will be open for a month but of course we're hoping to reach the funding goal well before then    Quote from: lobat999 on October 28, 2017, 11:35:32 PM Quote from: Rigorous on October 28, 2017, 09:41:24 PM Quote from: kraterion on October 28, 2017, 08:04:38 PM Quote from: Rigorous on October 28, 2017, 01:31:08 PM Quote from: SEELE^^01 on October 28, 2017, 10:25:25 AM the ico is just for raising funds to start with the work, if you think you can make fast money, i would not to advise to buy, because this token is for the longterm and not shortterm.  make your homeworks, dudes & dudettes  That cannot be stressed enough.  The development will take roughly a year.  People on this forum tend to get a heart attack after just 1 week of silence from the developers. That is not always without good reason. The least you can do after your ICO is to celebrate reaching the minimum cap and even that does not always happen. And sadly in some cases they have disappeared completely.  But to give weekly updates, let alone daily ones, a whole year long... I would be impressed if GATCOIN manages to keep that up. It would be very encouraging if they do.  Weekly updates? I'll be very happy if they deliver monthly updates lol. Btw with the current state of ICO market you can't do quick moneys, you must choose wisely and keep your tokens for long term  There is not even a need to do development updates, just a weekly sign of life. For example in the form of blog posts. Could even be random facts about loyalty programs. As long as investors are assured the team did not ran off with the money.  Naturally, every investor want assurance from DEVS that they are in good hands.  We've tried hard to be active and transparent so far and we hope to keep this up during development after the ICO too! Maybe not weekly updates but certainly when major milestones are reached as well as progress along the way. We know that your support is earned through our clear and regular communication and will certainly keep that up. You all are helping to make GATCOIN real!

Author: Rigorous
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Something is bugging me about that review:  The company cites immaturity of the Ethereum network as a primary risk. This is not entirely unfounded, given the long-standing challenges facing Ethereum’s mainstream development. The Ethereum network has already been prone to significant processing delays due to extremely high volumes. It seems like Gatcoin’s success would exacerbate processing delays on the network, especially if mass adoption is achieved. To date, it is unclear how or if the Ethereum community can resolve these issues.  The author does not take the high-speed Super Large Ledgers into account which separate the Merchant Token transactions from the Ethereum network. The risks outlined in the whitepaper pertain to GATCOIN transations mainly. I concede the GATCOIN platform being a D-app on Ethereum could be vulnerable, and I am not sure to what degree the Merchant Token networks can continue to run autonomously in the event Ethereum underperforms.  However, the Ethereum Byzantium upgrade has cleared up Ethereum network congestions and lowered the transaction fees dramatically. And there are even more upgrades in the pipeline.

It is really not that different from the tradings cards and sticker books they have now.

Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Hey Community! Sorry I have been away for so long but as you are about to see we have been very busy. Please take a look at some exciting new announcements here https://www.gatcoin.io/update-on-gatcoin-private-sale-public-pre-sale-and-public-sale/  To summarise; Pre Sale is starting October 28th with a 20% bonus! 15 Million GAT Coins will be available over the pre sale period at a price of $0.167 USD (price fixed in ETH) to reward all of you who have been waiting patiently! Make sure to sign up to our mailing list to ensure you get in on time!  We have been working hard on our demonstration app, but to make sure that investors get to preview the functionality of the GAT Wallet, purchasing process in the GAT Marketplace and the trading mechanics of the GAT Exchange we have pushed back the Public Sale date to December 15th, when 115 Million GAT Coins will go on sale for $0.20 USD (price fixed in ETH).  The development process has given us clarity on the cost of business rollout and we have adjusted Hard Cap accordingly it has been reduced to $35.87 Million USD so  no more tiered ICO structure.  As some of you will have noticed this leaves 70 Million GAT Coins unspoken for, due to overwhelming demand for private sales, we are in discussions with several parties, we have allocated this for private sales (with a 6 month lock in period) to ensure public investors still have ample opportunity to participate but still allow institutional investment.  That covers everything but please make sure to sign up on telegram https://t.me/gatcoin and the mailing list https://www.gatcoin.io/sign-up/ to make sure you stay up to date and don't miss out on any potential promotions

Body: They thought of that. GAT will try to keep the coin stable.  The GAT Foundation will control the supply and circulation of GAT Coins in the open market. The GAT Foundation will also act as market-maker and regulator on the GAT Exchange.  Initially, 10% of the GAT Coins in circulation will be allocated to the GAT Foundation as a reserve for open-market operations.  The stated goals of the GAT Foundation are to:   ▪ Ensure a stable and transparent price for GAT Coins in order to assist merchants accurately price goods, services and incentives   ▪ Ensure liquidity of GAT Coins within the GAT System so that the GAT Coin can remain a useful settlement currency for the exchange of Merchant Tokens   ▪ Manage a sufficient reserve of alternative crypto-currencies to conduct open-market operations to support the price of GAT Coins   It is almost like a central bank!

Author: ben_GAT
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Apologies for the delayed reply. This is a very excellent point and we’re glad you looked so thoroughly through our white paper to find it. The data you cited from Visa represents the STRESS testing and PEAK transaction speeds that Visa can handle—for example, AliPay can currently handle 180k TPS at peak. However, the average TPS for Visa is still in the 4,000-5,000 range. Our figures in the white paper are for our average as well. We can handle up to 100k TPS for short periods (such as holidays like you mentioned) but we feel reporting this number gives a false impression of our capabilities and that average is much more important. No company can reliably offer 47,000 TPS as an average. Even Ethereum Enterprise which is aiming for just 100 TPS has yet to reach it. We feel this is really one of the hidden strengths of GATCOIN.

In that case I am interesting in how the user interface for configuring and managing Merchant Tokens looks.

Author: Rigorous
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: The danger lies in "there is no limit to the results that you could gather from a growing set of data." You can combine and massage data in any way you want to get any result that is desired.  Risking a Godwin, here is an example:  Chillingly, there can be no question that the Geheime Staatspolizei’s aura of omniscience was due in no small measure to its special competence in gathering and organizing huge quantities of data on resistance movements, potentially subversive individuals, informers, industrial firms, publications, even other security agencies, and making that information readily accessible to its field agents through an ingeniously contrived system of multi-colored index cards. One shudders to think what the Gestapo might have done with just a handful of the data-mining tools currently employed by the NSA.  And:  the "only way to protect the people’s privacy is not to allow the government to collect their information in the first place.”  http://www.businessinsider.com/stasi-talks-about-nsa-surveillance-state-2013-6  Or perhaps more relevant to us:  “Miners are getting jailed and accused of terrorism, money laundering, computer crimes and many other crimes,” read one comment from a user who claimed to be Venezuelan.  https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2017/03/10/bitcoin-mining-is-big-business-in-venezuela-but-the-government-wants-to-shut-it-down/  Filling in those PC hardware cashback forms with your name and address could land you in trouble. If GATCOIN has a way to redeem rewards without giving away that much personal information, that would be a boon for privacy.

Author: Affchain
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: I like the project and all but there is some information in the whitepaper that is pulled from some very old reports on the transaction speeds of VISA.  Whitepaper    2004 https://www.informationweek.com/visa-tests-transaction-processing-system/d/d-id/1026381  During the annual weeklong stress test, conducted at an IBM facility outside Washington, D.C., Visa ran the system at a processing load of 6,200 transaction messages per second, a 20% increase over last year's peak on Dec. 24 of 5,200 transaction messages per second. Each card purchase requires about two transaction messages.   2013 https://www.visa.com/blogarchives/us/2013/10/10/stress-test-prepares-visanet-for-the-most-wonderful-time-of-the-year/index.html  After the test is concluded, the VisaNet team determines the best configuration to maintain our higher levels of security and reliability when millions of transactions from all over the world hit the network during the holiday shopping season. As a result, they also come back from Gaithersburg with a number that represents the maximum processing capacity VisaNet can handle, which later is stamped on coffee mugs and distributed to the team involved in the test. This year’s “mug number” – as we like to call it – is 47,000 transaction messages per second, which is a huge step forward from 2012’s peak capacity of 30,000 transaction messages per second!   I didn't have time to look up the current transactions per second capabilities of VISA so don't quote me on this but I vaguely remember hearing Vitalek say they were over 69,000 TPS. The 5,000 TPS capabilities are from 14 years old data. Please correct me if I'm wrong. I'm no expert in this field. I decided to do a quick search after thinking about Vitalek the Visitor's talk a few months back.  So my question to GATCOIN is, who looked up and verified your whitepaper's numbers? My next question is.... Is your tech ready to handle the load of the holidays? With November and December comes a tripling of TPS at the minimum.    That is a small typo if anything and in my opinion does not reflect the capabilities of this project as a whole. Nor does it raise any red flags. After reading through the whitepaper again I actually saw the brilliance behind this idea and I am still a supporter. Just thought I'd point this out to see how the team reacts and also to have it brought light by a supporter rather than a trolly nay-sayer.

Body: Another example is medical data. For example, if hospitals combined all data on cancer treatments and cancer patients, there could be more effective treatments. The reason is that cancer is commonly treated in a one-size-fits-all fashion (tons of chemo and radiation) instead of a personalized treatment based on the type of cancer and its location among other characteristics.  But many hospitals prefer to sit on their data, which by the way is often stored in a non-standard proprietary format too. This situation is not helped by privacy advocates fighting medical databases.  https://www.statnews.com/2017/06/06/data-sharing-cancer-treatment/  Now we are straying far away from GATCOIN's area but I think the message that analyzing consumer data could provide a mutual benefit is clear.

Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: That ties in with my earlier question, what is the reason for collecting all that data on those cashback forms? I suspect companies want to collect data to analyze customer behavior. From the companies' point of view if GATCOIN prevented the collection of personal data, that would be a loss for them.  Section 2.2.7 of the whitepaper is relevant:  Consumption Patterns: by analyzing geo-location and token consumption from the GAT Wallet, enterprises will gain valuable insight into where marketing resources are best applied  Since the app is on a smartphone it would be technically possible to extract personal data (anonymized or not - and we have known for long that "anonymized" data really isn't).  Therefore, from the consumers' point of view it would be interesting to know GATCOIN's stance how to serve both the companies' and customers' needs with regards to marketing and privacy.

Author: Rigorous
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: No, that was just an example. But I do have some experience with Asus promos.  When I tried to redeem an Asus promo code, I had to pick one of their regional redemption sites. I bought an Asus product in a shop in a different country which shipped it to me. When I tried to submit the form for the region of my country, it would not continue to the next page nor show an error. When I emailed customer support they said it could be a browser error. On several website other people had problems redeeming their Asus promo codes, as it appears the redemption sites went offline or 'out of stock' in the weekends.  Eventually I started to use my brain and went to fill in the form at the redemption site for the region of the shop where I bought the product. And that worked.  So I am an idiot. But still, Asus should have displayed helpful errors. They could have been more clear which one of their regional websites to use. Or better yet, have a single universal redemption site.  ----  Another personal experience is with a different brand, Bosch (they make home appliances and tools). After sending them the invoice, they mailed me they could not read it. They asked me to resubmit the invoice through a different form. Apparently it is not possible to use the original form to resubmit the invoice, it causes a 'serial number not found' error. At first I got a form that did not even contain proper labels, just placeholders. The form itself did not work either. A few weeks later I tried again. The labels were fixed and I tried saving the invoice as JPG, GIF, BMP, PNG and PDF, but the result is always the same: "Failed to upload your invoice". As of today this has not been resolved.

We have not designed GAT Coin to be used as an in store payment currency, instead we want users to trade GAT Coin for tokens/vouchers/rewards from their favourite retailers. Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: No merchant tokens will be entirely electronic, don't worry we are trying to have less useless things in your wallet not more!  Quote from: pynetx on October 02, 2017, 05:45:33 AM Will gatcoin also implement affiliate earnings with regard to coupons and deals?   At this time the model does not include affiliate earnings, but this might be a feature that we consider if there is demand for it from the merchant side.  Quote from: Vikingr on October 02, 2017, 05:51:39 AM  From this project details I got the idea that this platform will give opportunity to each store to use their own token. Is it? If that s the case then I will like to know that what will be the benefit of this system to the holders/investors of gatcoin? I have a little confusion in this point otherwise I like the idea to have that project and to invest in it. I hope you will clear this confusion.  Yes we will give merchants a chance to issue their own tokens as rewards and vouchers. These tokens can only be used in the store of that particular merchant or sold on the GAT Exchange for GAT Coins.  This is where the value of GAT Coin is, if you want to buy points for your favourite coffee place or more airmiles to get an upgraded ticket, you need to have GAT Coins to purchase them from other users on the GAT Exchange. The only place to buy Gatcoins is via our ICO or off ICO investors afterwards. The more people on the GAT Exchange and the more Merchants on the GAT System the higher the demand for GAT Coins. Which is great for early investors because we already have an anchor client with over 60,000 retail locations on board!  Quote from: Frank37 on October 02, 2017, 08:23:21 AM Quote from: Elkmar on October 02, 2017, 08:13:57 AM Good to know there is a mobile app, people spend less and less time on their computer and most of their time on the phone now.  More time on phone is the first reason, the second will be at local stores you generally don't have a computer with you. Or will the system only be available for online stores and not be spreaded to local stores? Couldn't find something about.  The system will be for online and offline, the A-Drop system allows merchants to drop coins in a geographic location which will benefit offline locations, we envisions merchants holding treasure hunts with various vouchers and the end destination being their store or event. Pokemon Go with real world prizes! Additionally the A-drop system will let merchants to send tokens directly in to the wallets of their target customers, like an electronics chain sending a promotion to every male, who has spent more than $500 on electronics in the last year in New York. This can drive traffic to both online and offline stores!  This system is explained in our System Overview https://www.gatcoin.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/170928v2-GATCOIN-System-Overview.pdf

Author: ben_GAT
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: There are a lot of great reasons to support GATCOIN! You can find a quick video here that explains the purpose: https://youtu.be/qq0_WVK8lMc  Also, our white paper goes into a lot of detail: https://www.gatcoin.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/170919v2-Whitepaper-EN.pdf  But to give a quick summary… GATCOIN will create a single platform to organize rewards points and discounts for all merchants and retailers. Customers who get rewards points from different companies (for example, hotels and coffee shops) can keep these in their app/wallet and trade the points on the GAT Exchange for the goods and services they truly want. Merchants gain more marketing options and can target customers based on age, demographics, and spending habits. Also, GATCOIN offers the airdrop feature to release coins to potential customers within a certain area and based on demographic/spending criteria. Moreover, we are designing this to be an easy-to-use, turnkey solution for retailers so that companies who aren’t tech savvy can get setup on the platform fast.  Of course, this all depends on the size of the network of retailers using GATCOIN. Fortunately, we already have a partnership with SK Planet Japan so that when we launch the full platform it will immediately be used at 21 major international and local brands in Japan with a network of over 30,000 retail stores, 80,000 restaurants and 60,000 beauty outlets.  If you want to stay on top of information about GATCOIN as it comes out (such as new features and exchanges announcements), please join our mailing list here: https://www.gatcoin.io/sign-up/

Author: ben_GAT
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Hi kraterion, sorry to have missed that. Yes, you are exactly correct in how the system would work.  We have a video which covers the process here: https://youtu.be/qq0_WVK8lMc  As to your second question, we will be in development until mid-2018. The public launch of the GATCOIN beta platform will be in June 2018 with the official launch of the Wallet and Marketplace in October 2018. The timeline is on page 29 of the white paper found here: https://www.gatcoin.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/170919v2-Whitepaper-EN.pdf  Although there are some other coins in this arena, we have found none which provide the same unified network of merchant rewards on one platform. Additionally, with our partnership with SK Planet Japan, we will launch the platform next year into a network of over 30,000 retail stores, 80,000 restaurants and 60,000 beauty outlets.

Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: It is important to note that the GAT Foundation is seperate from the Dev's, the entire purpose of the GAT Foundation is to be a non profit that ensures the longevity of GAT Coin and the GAT Exchange, so in no way would it ever be in their interest to dump all their GAT Coins at once and ruin the market. It is also important to note that we as the Dev's will not have access to the GAT Coins allocated to the GAT Foundation, so we could not cash in like that even if we wanted to (we don't btw all of us are personally invested in the project and firmly believe in the future of the project).  Your suggestion that we elaborate more on the GAT Foundation, its purpose and its strategy is an excellent one, we will work on that and keep you all updated once it is online!  Quote from: haxllega on September 30, 2017, 11:57:10 AM $20 M USD is really a lot. Why do they need as much? I think it will be very hard to achieve this amounts of funds.  Short answer, we want to do this right, in order or ICO investors to see truly excellent returns on their investment we need to build a bullet proof system, test it extensively set up infrastructure in multiple markets and actively pursue as many merchants as possible to expand the network as soon as possible. To do this we need funds unfortunately we cant build a easy to use interactive marketplace that spans the globe and covers a vast network  overnight and on the cheap   If you look at section 4.3.1 you will find more information about the use of proceeds and our expansion plan.  https://www.gatcoin.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/170919v2-Whitepaper-EN.pdf  Quote from: levyashin on September 30, 2017, 02:48:59 PM I have a question about merchant tokens.  So if they want a side market about their tokens it can put it to exchanges, right?  X brand make a token and people loving it, so a user can put it at least etherdelta to make a profit of it?   At the moment there is no mechanism in place to allow them to take merchant tokens directly to a marketplace. Merchant tokens can be used to purchase goods in store, on line or traded on GAT Marketplace.  It is helpful to view Merchant tokens more like traditional rewards vouchers, not a currency or a stored value card. This is where the value of the GAT Exchange comes in where consumers can take the additional step of monetizing rewards if they wish to and if there is demand for it.  We have an overview presentation https://www.gatcoin.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/170928v2-GATCOIN-System-Overview.pdf that explains the system concisely.

Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Unsold tokens from the ICO will revert to the GAT Foundation which is independent so I cannot say what their plans will be. However the main purpose of the GAT Foundation is to ensure that the GAT Market remains stable and that GAT Coins remain liquid within the GAT System so they continue to be the currency of the GAT Exchange. So its safe to assume they will not just dump the tokens and dilute the market!  I also hope we hit the hard cap and this question takes care of itself!  Quote from: matjas on September 30, 2017, 08:54:17 AM Nowadays a lot of retailers use some kind of benefits programs trough cards, coupons, etc. But i noticed that even thou the company is international and it has branches all over Europe, your loyalty card or coupons are useless outside of the country of issue. How will Gatcoin work around this?  You are right under a traditional rewards system you can't use, say your coffee rewards points from Germany in Hong Kong. In the GATCOIN System you would be able to work around this. Here is how. Say you are moving countries and want to make sure you don't lose all the value you have in your loyalty programs, the solution is take these tokens to the GAT Exchange and sell them there for GAT Coin. You can then use this GAT Coin to purchase merchant tokens for your destination country or even for an airline to help pay for your trip!

Author: ben_GAT
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: While, technically, it is possible for companies to establish a blockchain token independently on their own, that alone is not doing them much use. The value of GATCOIN comes from its network and the GAT Exchange. For customers, collecting blockchain rewards points from various retailers/shops/merchants doesn’t solve the issue that they have points that they can’t/don’t want to use. Through the growing network of retailers (big and small) on the GATCOIN network, these customers will have greater choice of how and where to use their rewards points (of course done via exchange through the GAT Exchange). Moreover, with all these customers of various merchants using the same wallet, it is easier for merchants to reach new customers (for example through demographic/spending targeting).  As we have already secured the partnership with SK Planet Japan, we are launching out of the gate with a strong network of merchants who will issue Tokens, thus offering immediate choice to consumers and GAT Wallet holders. As new merchants come on board, we streamline the process for them so that blockchain tokens are no longer an onerous technical issue for them but rather just another marketing application—we remove the hassle of having to Google the process and learn the tech.  To put it simply, we are offering a one-stop-shop for all rewards points. The more merchants who join, the more powerful the platform. We are working hard to recruit even more partners and are confident that more merchants will join the platform organically as the success of GATCOIN grows.

Body: Correct, however, it won't be an exact one-for-one exchange. It's better to think of it as a marketplace where people have Merchant Tokens they wish to exchange but must be bought and sold in GAT Coins. Thus, depending on the demand and merchant-dictated redeemable value of their Tokens, you could, for example exchange 5 tokens from merchant A for just 1 token from merchant B. And this is intuitive--for example, if merchant A were a coffee shop and merchant B were an airline.

Author: Rigorous
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: The example in the whitepaper demonstrates an ideal scenario where the rewards effectively used to stimulate customers into spending more, so that there is a higher net profit.  My assumption with loyalty programs was that unredeemed rewards were accounted for. That is, the merchant gives rewards that are likely to go unredeemed instead of giving real discounts.  By making the loyalty program interaction more user friendly and efficient, isn't there a risk customers redeeming a bigger percentage of their rewards without fully compensating it with additional spending, thereby driving down net profits?

Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Excellent point, you are correct in traditional loyalty programs a certain percentage goes unredeemed and this is built in to the model.  However we believe that  when you make things more user friendly and efficient there is a net gain as it encourages spending, increases engagement and aids in customer acquisition, especially with the additional features that allow merchants to target users via demographics, spending habits and location (for example males aged 35-30 that frequent coffee shops within the city of Sydney). An additional feature is that merchants can choose to accept a combination of merchant tokens and FIAT when selling goods, so items bought with merchant tokens are not necessarily given away for free but rather sold at a discounted price.  We also believe, and I think most people on this forum would agree, that there is a an inherently interesting quality about crypto, and that many people will enjoy the collecting and trading aspect of the system and that this will in turn drive up engagement for merchants.

Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: A point well taken if merchant tokens could be converted directly into products from other merchants but they can not.  For example Merchant A issues vouchers to Customer X, Customer X sells these tokens to Customer Y and uses the proceeds to by vouchers for Merchant B and buys something from Merchant B's store and Customer Y uses the original vouchers in Merchant A's store.  Who looses out in this situation? No one, The voucher Merchant A originally issued are still being spent in their store, Customers X and Y are getting exactly the products they wanted and merchants A and B are making sales that they might not have in a traditional rewards system!  Merchant tokens can only be sold to other parties that want them, so while the consumer may be converting them in to rewards from other companies they can only do so if someone else wants the tokens in the first place.

Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: GAT Coins are not investment products, they will however be tradable on exchanges for other cryptos and will be the primary currency of the GAT Marketplace.  For example if a Merchant was offering vouchers that you wanted to take advantage of but had not earned or if you needed a few extra to claim the reward. You could purchase those vouchers from another user on the GAT Marketplace, but only if you have GAT Coin. So no the interest is not from the Merchant side it is from the consumer side.  The fact that there is a limited supply of GAT Coin means that one can reasonably expect the value to rise as demand for it increases as more Merchants and users adopt the technology, we believe that this offers an excellent value proposition for people that buy GAT Coin now at a low fixed rate as opposed to later on the open market.  You are right that the language is deliberate. We have worked very hard with our Skadden, Arps our lawyers to ensure absolute transparency with our proceedings and to make sure we follow all regulatory guidelines in our target markets. We want everyone who purchases GAT Coin to be clear on what they are buying and the company behind it.

Author: ben_GAT
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: Great question. GATCOIN’s benefit to customers is that all Merchant Tokens are tradeable on the GAT Exchange. So, as you say, they might earn with Shopkick but the points will not mean much if the customer isn’t interested in the merchant—whereas with GATCOIN Merchant Tokens, the customer can trade. Moreover, GATCOIN offers merchants the opportunity to reach new customers. This would work in the case when a customer already has the GATCOIN app for rewards with company A and now passes by an airdrop location for company B. Now that customer collects Merchant Tokens for company B. He or she might choose to shop with company B or just trade those tokens for tokens with company A. Lastly, airdrop can be very targeted for merchants: rather than making these airdrop Merchant Tokens available to all customers, they can be selectively released to customers in a specific demographic match or those with particular spending habits. This data will be collected from the GATCOIN app which customers use to hold and collect Merchant Tokens.  There is more detail about this functionality here: https://www.gatcoin.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/170928v2-GATCOIN-System-Overview.pdf

Author: Islapdonkey
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: No company is going to want to form a partnership and make a lifetime payment, for a service they can create themselves in less than 30mins. That's just a fact. No matter how much you guys might sugarcoat it, the idea is nothing new to the space.  There are several companies already offering this services and every one of them is doing poorly in the market.    If a company wants a coin, they could easily create a coin on wallet builder or on several other services that offer this and have it listed in an exchange in a few days. Companies can also create a wave token and have it on wave dex immediately or erc 20 and have it on delta immediately. With implementation of the new protocol, the transaction will really speed up. so even if Gatcoin gain better traction than the troves of companies offering similar ideas, the idea will be obsolete in a few months to a yr. Solidarity might be in infancy but if I a non technical observer can create erc token. am quite sure a company with interest in blockchain can easily figure it out.  So I know it's on a lot of ppl interest to shill without reserve but I won't let you lie to unaware investor and make it seem like this is a groundbreaking idea, cos you are basically leading them to a trap, that I think, will end up costing long term holders dearly. If someone wants to take chance and  pnd the ico, that I can understand but this idea is nothing new, it's already been offered by a lot of companies, and is almost obsolete cos the mass is becoming better aware of the blockchain tech.   This is akin to buying a new telly, then investing into a robotic model whose  job is to ONLY control the remote, cos you haven't figured out how to do it yourself. How long do you anticipate a need for that robot?

Body: You are right that any company can just create their own ERC-20 token. The downside of that is you get an evergrowing list of tokens that you have to remember why and what you even have them for. If this project here, has strong enough marketing and builds the right partnerships, they can attract many big names companies to adopt their token as the rewards token of choice. This brings a form of limited centralization into the picture but is that always a bad thing? The word centralized has almost become a taboo because of the decentralization movement. Sometimes, in regards to organization, decentralization of every business sector and industry out there could get a little bit discombobulated. For example, I love checking all my emails from all my accounts on one list and on one screen. I could care less if I have to give Google access to all that data, it saves me hours of valuable time every day.

Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: White paper seemed to be written by Balzac. It is necessary to read it for two days. Balzac wrote long novels because he was paid for every page. Now I've reading your white paper, but it's only up to 3/4 again. What I liked: internal Merchant Tokens are accessed only inside the system, your GAT Coins, which is the ERC20 token, serves as the input and output to the system. As far as I understand, Merchant Tokens are being accessed at a much faster rate than the Ethereum network can provide. The speed of transactions like in Visa / Mastercard is a huge advantage. Author: GAT_Chris
Title: 🌟 ⚡🚀ANN: GATCOIN Blockchain Rewards Program [Presale on 28 October]🌟 ⚡🚀
Body: If we were simply providing branded ERC 20 tokens I would agree with you. But we are not, we are providing a system where merchants can issue vouchers as rewards, airdrop them as incentives and modify them as required for individual promotion programs. For consumers we are providing a marketplace to trade these rewards and wallet to consolidate various rewards programs.  We are lowering substantially some of the barriers to entry that the average mainstream consumer faces with the adoption of blockchain technology by increasing transaction speeds and delivering blockchain to them via trusted retailers in a manner they already know (like a coffee reward card or frequent flyer program) all within a simple mobile interface.  GATCOIN provides a complete ecosystem that benefits merchants by giving them an exciting new way to incentivise and entice customers (and gain valuable data on spending habits) and consumers by providing a way to consolidate multiple rewards platforms with the added benefit of being able to convert rewards/and vouchers into crypto on the open market.

Body: Whilst much of the team has a China connection we are not  a Chinese team, so are fear not we are not affected any regulation changes in China.  The platform provides mainstream merchants and retailers the opportunity to give their customers blockchain based rewards/vouchers. These rewards can then be used by consumers to redeem/purchase items from the issuing merchant like traditional rewards. One of the key features that makes our system different is that consumers can choose to trade these rewards/vouchers on the open market for GAT Coin which can then be traded for other merchant rewards or for other crypto such as ETH or BTC.  Stay tuned for more announcement in the coming hours on another key feature that differentiates GATCOIN from other projects.
